Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createMarker(25.10)                                        createMarker(25.10)

Name
       createMarker - Creates markers for violations in the database

Syntax
       createMarker

       [-help]

       [-bbox  {  <x1  y1  x2 y2> } | -poly {{ <x1 y1 x2 y2> ...} | { <x1 y1>}
       {<x2 y2>} ...}}]

       [-desc <description>]

       [-layer {layerName | layerNumber}]

       [-rulemap]

       [-subtype <subtypeName>]

       [-tool <toolName>]

       [-type <typeName>]

       Creates markers for violations in the database.  Use  this  command  to
       create  a  specific marker that has been created by a third party tool.
       The created markers can be saved and  restored  by  saveDesign/restore-
       Design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each createMarker parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man createMarker

       -bbox <x1 y1 x2 y2>
              Specifies  the area of the bounding box of the marker. For exam-
              ple, createMarker -bbox 100 100 100.5 100.5.

              Type: Real

       -desc <description>
              Describes the marker. For example, createMarker -desc "the  user
              mark is non default rule spacing check".

              Default: ""

              Type: String

       -layer {layerName | layerNumber}
              Specifies the layer. Following are few examples:

              * createMarker -layer METAL2 creates a marker on layer METAL2.

              * createMarker -layer VIA3 creates a marker on cut layer VIA3.

              * createMarker -layer 4 creates a marker on layer METAL4.

              Type: String

       -poly {{ <x1 y1 x2 y2> ...} | { <x1 y1>} {<x2 y2>} ...}}
              Specifies the area of the bounding polygon of the marker.

       -rulemap
              Specifies if the marker needs to be created through ruleMap.

       -subtype <subtypeName>
              Specifies the marker subtype. For example, createMarker -subtype
              user_spacing.

              Default: Other

              Type: String

       -tool <toolName>
              Specifies  the  source  software  application. For example, cre-
              ateMarker -tool Calibre.

              Default: Other

              Type: String

       -type <typeName>
              Specifies the  marker  type.  For  example,  createMarker  -type
              user_verify.

              Default: Other

              Type: String

Example
              * The  following command generates a marker for tool named Cali-
                bre with type METAL1 and subtype S.1:

                createMarker -bbox { 1 2 1 2  }  -tool  Calibre  -type  METAL1
                -subtype S.1

                The violation browser displays the marker in the above example
                as follows:

                + Calibre

                    + METAL1

                        + S.1

                            ...

              * Suppose  the cadence LPA tool has created the following marker
                on layer METAL3:

                CDNLitho;SPACING; Severity: 3; MARKER_INFO: "CD = 45.39"

                bbox = (468.248, 63.511) (468.310, 63.599)

                The following command creates a corresponding  marker  in  the
                Innovus design:

                createMarker  -bbox  {468.248  63.511  468.310  63.599} -layer
                metal3 \

                             -type CDNLitho -subtype Spacing

              *

                The following command generates a polygon  shape  marker  with
                the user description:

                createMarker  -poly {100.0 100.0 194.0 100.0 194.0 238.0 168.0
                238.0 168.0 288.0 100.0 288.0} \

                -tool User -desc "congested area"

Related Information
       The Identifying and Viewing Violations chapter of User Guide.

